# Onshape Mass Properties

Computed physical properties of solid geometry: **volume, mass, surface area
(periphery), centroid, and the inertia tensor**. Onshape integrates these over the
Parasolid bodies of a Part Studio, a single part, or a whole assembly. This is the
canonical jd for the `massproperties` endpoints that @onshape/partstudios,
@onshape/parts, and @onshape/assemblies reference, and the standard **verify**
primitive used by @onshape/api (compare volume before/after an edit).

## Model

Addressed by the shared `did/{wvm}/{wvmid}/eid` family (see @onshape/api) — substitute
`/w/` (workspace) with `/v/` or `/m/` to read a version/microversion. All three
endpoints are **read-only GETs**. Three scopes, narrowing down:

- **Part Studio** — every solid in the tab. Optionally narrow with `partId` (repeatable).
- **Part** — one body, selected by the extra path segment `partid/{partid}`.
- **Assembly** — the aggregate over all instances; reports a `massMissingCount` when
  some instance lacks a density/material.

**Mass depends on material/density.** Volume and surface area are pure geometry;
`mass` is `volume × density`, so a part with no assigned material has `hasMass: false`
and a mass derived from a default density. Assign material in the UI or override via
`useMassPropertyOverrides`.

## Endpoints

| METHOD path | purpose |
|---|---|
| `GET /partstudios/d/{did}/{wvm}/{wvmid}/e/{eid}/massproperties` | mass props for a Part Studio |
| `GET /parts/d/{did}/{wvm}/{wvmid}/e/{eid}/partid/{partid}/massproperties` | mass props for one part |
| `GET /assemblies/d/{did}/{wvm}/{wvmid}/e/{eid}/massproperties` | aggregate mass props for an assembly |

Query params (per scope, from the slice):

- **Part Studio**: `partId` (narrow to bodies), `massAsGroup` (treat selected parts as
  one combined body vs. per-part results), `useMassPropertyOverrides`, `configuration`,
  `rollbackBarIndex`, `elementMicroversionId`, `linkDocumentId`.
- **Part**: `useMassPropertyOverrides`, `inferMetadataOwner`, `configuration`,
  `rollbackBarIndex`, `elementMicroversionId`, `linkDocumentId`.
- **Assembly**: `configuration`, `linkDocumentId`.

## Shapes

Part Studio and Part return a **`BTMassProperties`** keyed by body — the top-level
`bodies` map holds one entry per body id (use the part id as the key for a single part;
`massAsGroup`/Part Studio aggregate folds into a synthetic key per spec):

```json
{
  "bodies": {
    "JHD": {
      "hasMass": true,
      "mass":             [0.7843, 0.7843, 0.7843],
      "volume":           [9.99e-5, 9.99e-5, 9.99e-5],
      "periphery":        [0.0276, 0.0276, 0.0276],
      "centroid":         [0.025, 0.0, 0.0125,  0.025, 0.0, 0.0125,  0.025, 0.0, 0.0125],
      "inertia":          [/* 9-element 3x3 tensor, value/low/high interleaved */],
      "principalInertia": [1.2e-5, 8.0e-6, 8.0e-6],
      "principalAxes":    [{"x":1,"y":0,"z":0}, {"x":0,"y":1,"z":0}, {"x":0,"y":0,"z":1}]
    }
  },
  "microversionId": "a1b2c3…"
}
```

Assembly returns the **flattened aggregate** (no `bodies` map) plus `massMissingCount`:

```json
{
  "mass":             [number],
  "volume":           [number],
  "periphery":        [number],
  "centroid":         [number],
  "inertia":          [number],
  "principalInertia": [number],
  "principalAxes":    [BTVector3d],
  "hasMass":          boolean,
  "massMissingCount": integer
}
```

`periphery` is total surface area; `centroid` and `inertia` are in document units about
the origin; `principalInertia` + `principalAxes` give the diagonalised tensor.

## Numbers — value + error bounds

Every scalar comes back as a **`[value, lowerBound, upperBound]`** array, not a bare
number — Onshape reports the numerical-integration tolerance band. So `volume[0]` is
the value; `volume[1]`/`volume[2]` bracket it. Vectors flatten the same way: `centroid`
is `[x, x_lo, x_hi, y, y_lo, y_hi, z, z_lo, z_hi]`. **Units are explicit** and SI by
default (volume m³, mass kg, area m², length m) regardless of the document's display
units. Read `value`, ignore the bounds unless you care about tolerance.

## Recipe — get volume + verify (READ-ONLY)

Basic auth per @onshape/auth (`$ONSHAPE_ACCESS_KEY:$ONSHAPE_SECRET_KEY` over HTTPS,
local testing only — production signs with HMAC). kb2 reference doc ids inline.

```bash
DID=378e93b0ad360aa043a0220b
WID=09273312fedee7bf3c3482ad
EID=a77918b06d5131918477a269
BASE=https://cad.onshape.com/api/v10

resp=$(curl -fsS -u "$ONSHAPE_ACCESS_KEY:$ONSHAPE_SECRET_KEY" \
  "$BASE/partstudios/d/$DID/w/$WID/e/$EID/massproperties")

# verify: a solid Part Studio must have positive volume on at least one body
vol=$(echo "$resp" | jq '[.bodies[].volume[0]] | add')
echo "total volume = $vol m^3"
awk -v v="$vol" 'BEGIN { exit !(v > 0) }' \
  && echo "OK: volume > 0" \
  || { echo "FAIL: empty/zero geometry"; exit 1; }
```

Before/after **edit verify** (the @onshape/api pattern): capture `vol` above, make the
edit through @onshape/api, re-run this GET, and assert the new volume differs as
expected. The `massproperties` GET is the trusted oracle that the geometry actually
changed — features-tree readback alone only proves the parameter, not the resulting solid.

